      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 839: `setPublishedAddressSettings` writes both published address and port on every disappear even when neither value changed. This can trigger unnecessary daemon updates and account reconfiguration while simply navigating back. Match the existing STUN/TURN pattern by only sending changed keys, and return if there are none.\n```suggestion\n        var detailsToUpdate \u003d [String: String]()\n        for (key, value) in settings {\n            let property \u003d ConfigKeyModel(withKey: key)\n            guard details.get(withConfigKeyModel: property) !\u003d value else { continue }\n            details.set(withConfigKeyModel: property, withValue: value)\n            detailsToUpdate[key.rawValue] \u003d value\n        }\n\n        guard !detailsToUpdate.isEmpty else { return }\n```",
